# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - Agents/Orgs: Linked to resources, applications, tickets, changes.
# - Locations: Linked to resources.
# - Product Models: Linked to resources.
# - Resources: Linked to agents, locations, product models, network interfaces, applications, services, events, tickets, changes.
# - Network Interfaces: Linked to resources, network links.
# - Network Links: Linked to network interfaces, resources, agents.
# - Applications/Modules: Linked to resources, agents, services, events, tickets, changes.
# - Services: Linked to applications/modules, tickets, changes.
# - Event Records: Linked to resources, applications, agents, tickets, operation plans.
# - Trouble Tickets: Linked to services, applications, resources, agents, events, notes, attachments.
# - Trouble Ticket Notes: Linked to trouble tickets, agents, procedure executions.
# - Change Requests: Linked to services, applications, resources, agents, attachments.
# - Operation Plans: Linked to pre/post conditions, event records.
# - Anomaly Patterns: Linked to event records, operation plans.
# - Document Attachments: Linked to trouble tickets, change requests.

# All entities seem to be well-connected. The graph is dense and covers various aspects of the NORIA vocabulary.
